"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387259","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-07","<p>The contract with Capita to provide Personal Independence Payment Assessments was awarded following a negotiated procurement route which offered an opportunity to clarify and probe bidders’ proposals during an extensive period of negotiation. The value of the contract, specification, redacted terms and conditions and schedules were published on Contracts Finder in the usual way on 01 November 2012.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-07T09:53:37.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387259/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387259/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-02","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will publish the contract his Department holds with Capita to provide personal independence payment assessments.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","5470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387260","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-07","<p>Cumbria County Council does receive funding from the New Homes Bonus. The allocation for the year 2015/16 was £1,324,888.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-07T14:01:18.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387260/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387260/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-02","Housing: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if his Department will allow Cumbria County Council to receive revenue from the new homes bonus.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","5268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387261","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-07","<p>I don't agree with the premise of the hon. Member's question. This Government is providing local authorities with the tools they need to grow their economies and rewarding authorities which support new businesses and housebuilding including Cumbria. Cumbria’s spending power in 2015-16 is £406.6 million, only 0.5% less than in 2014-15, and it will gain £1.3 million through the New Homes Bonus and £0.8 million in retained business rates income above the expected level.</p><p> </p><p>We recognise the additional challenges faced by the most rural authorities in delivering efficiencies and transforming services and have provided £1.1 million in Rural Services delivery funding to Cumbria in 2015-16.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-07T14:30:47.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387261/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387261/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-02","Local Government Finance: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what support his Department plans to provide to Cumbria County Council to make up their funding shortfall.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","5270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387262","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-07","<p>The Business Rates Retention scheme allows local authorities overall to keep 50% of the business rates collected within their area, including from the nuclear industry. Our Manifesto committed to promote localism by allowing councils to keep a higher proportion of the business rates revenue that is generated in their area.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-07T16:23:40.993Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387262/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387262/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-07-02","Non-domestic Rates: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if his Department will take steps to allow councils in Cumbria to keep funds raised by business rates from the nuclear industry.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","5357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387263","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-07","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","5349 ; 5350 ; 5378","2015-07-07T14:54:44.203Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387263/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387263/answer","PQ 5349 .pdf","PQ 5349 .pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Zero Hour Contracts","UKSA Letter to Member - Zero Hour Contracts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387263/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-02","Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people aged between 16 and 24 in (a) Jarrow constituency, (b) South Tyneside, (c) the North East and (d) the UK have been on zero-hours contracts in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","5377"
