"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387296","Department of Health","false","2015-07-08","<p>The table below shows the total National Health Service expenditure and total primary healthcare expenditure. The reason the tables are split is due to NHS revenue expenditure not being directly comparable across the time period from 1999-00 to 2013-14. The percentage of primary healthcare expenditure when compared to total NHS expenditure is shown in the last column.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The 2014-15 final outturn data is not yet available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table 1 shows years 1999-00 to 2007-08. The NHS expenditure figures are on a pre-Clear Line of Sight resource budgeting basis.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table 1</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Year</p></td><td><p>NHS Revenue Expenditure under pre Clear Line of Sight</p></td><td><p>Expenditure on Primary Healthcare</p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>Primary Healthcare Expenditure as a % of NHS Revenue Expenditure</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ billion</p></td><td><p>£ billion</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1999-00</p></td><td><p>39.29</p></td><td><p>10.69</p></td><td><p>27.21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2000-01</p></td><td><p>42.69</p></td><td><p>11.45</p></td><td><p>26.82</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2001-02</p></td><td><p>47.29</p></td><td><p>12.84</p></td><td><p>27.15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2002-03</p></td><td><p>56.90</p></td><td><p>13.71</p></td><td><p>24.10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2003-04</p></td><td><p>61.86</p></td><td><p>14.95</p></td><td><p>24.17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2004-05</p></td><td><p>66.87</p></td><td><p>16.59</p></td><td><p>24.81</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005-06</p></td><td><p>74.17</p></td><td><p>18.15</p></td><td><p>24.47</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006-07</p></td><td><p>78.47</p></td><td><p>18.63</p></td><td><p>23.74</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007-08</p></td><td><p>86.38</p></td><td><p>19.16</p></td><td><p>22.18</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table 2 shows years 2008-09 to 2013-14. NHS expenditure figures are on an aligned basis following the HM Treasury’s Clear Line of Sight programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table 2</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Year</p></td><td><p>NHS Revenue Expenditure under Clear Line of Sight Rules</p></td><td><p>Expenditure on Primary Healthcare</p></td><td><p>Rebased Expenditure on Primary Healthcare</p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>Primary Healthcare Expenditure as a % of NHS Revenue Expenditure</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ billion</p></td><td><p>£ billion</p></td><td><p>£ billion</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008-09</p></td><td><p>87.62</p></td><td><p>19.92</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>22.73</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>94.42</p></td><td><p>20.87</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>22.10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>97.47</p></td><td><p>21.37</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>21.92</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>100.27</p></td><td><p>21.64</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>21.58</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>102.57</p></td><td><p>21.43</p></td><td><p>21.29</p></td><td><p>20.76</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>106.50</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>21.32</p></td><td><p>20.02</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Notes:</em></p><p> </p><ol start="1" type="1"><li>These figures represent the amount of expenditure on the purchase Primary Healthcare by commissioners. This is in the context that primary care groups (years 1999-2000 to 2001-02), primary care trusts (years 2000-01 to 2012-13) health authorities (years 1999-2000 to 2001-02) and strategic health authorities (years 2002-03 to 2012-13) NHS England and clinical commissioning groups (2013-14 onwards) were responsible for commissioning healthcare from providers based on the needs of their local population.</li></ol><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ol start="2" type="1"><li>2012-13 expenditure figure have been re-based to allow for direct comparison to the 2013-14 expenditure figure which has been presented on a different basis according to accounting practices in NHS England.</li></ol><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-07-08T13:30:34.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387296/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387296/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-07-02","Primary Health Care: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much the NHS spent on primary care in England in each year since 2000; and what such figures are as a percentage of the total NHS budget.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","5428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387297","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>The Government set out in its Solar Strategy Part 2, published in April 2014, an ambition to install solar panels on the public sector estate. The Cabinet Office is working with other government departments to identify suitable projects.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-07-09T14:58:06.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387297/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387297/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-02","Solar Power: Public Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will take steps to identify effective ways to encourage public sector buildings to utilise roof space by installing solar panels.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","5266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387298","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>Her Majesty’s Passport Office deploys its workforce flexibly across different types of work in order to manage performance against service standards. As individual staff process several different types of application it is not possible to provide a breakdown of how many work solely on first time applications for children born overseas.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-09T14:48:24.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387298/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387298/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387298/answer/previousversion/11683","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Passports: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many members of staff worked in HM Passport Office processing applications for first passports for UK children born overseas in May (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014 and (f) 2015; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","5453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387299","Home Office","false","2015-07-20","<p>Information on the number of first time passports issued to children overseas and average processing times are set out in the table below.</p><p>Due to the way management information was captured previously it is not possible to provide comparative data for the number of passports issued to children overseas before January 2014 or a breakdown of processing times by country prior to January 2015.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-20T09:50:36.603Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387299/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387299/answer","PQ 5451 Gareth Thomas Processing Times 1st time child overseas apps v1.2(1).xlsx","PQ 5451 Gareth Thomas Processing Times 1st time child overseas apps v1.2(1).xlsx","First time passports issued to children","First time passports issued to children","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387299/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387299/answer/previousversion/11682","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Passports: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many first passports have been issued to British children born overseas in each of the last three years; what the average length of time was to process applications from each overseas country in each of the last three years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","5451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387300","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-10","<p>Network Rail has recently completed work to renew various overhead line components on the East Coast Main Line.　Particular focus has been between King's Cross and Hitchin where contact and catenary wire and droppers were replaced. This has resulted in improved performance. Network Rail are also delivering a £250 million project to enhance power supply on the southern part of the route.　This will allow the new Intercity Express and Thameslink trains to operate an enhanced service.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-10T11:28:15.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387300/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387300/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-02","East Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to make the East Coast Main Line more resilient to power line failures.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","5340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387301","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-10","<p>We do not hold information regarding power line failures to that level of disaggregation. Network Rail may have this information, and my Hon Friend may wish to contact them directly through Mark Carne, Chief Executive, Network Rail, 1 Eversholt Street, London, NW1 2DN.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","5339","2015-07-10T11:25:05.673Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387301/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387301/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-02","East Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many times there have been power line failures on the East Coast Main Line in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","5341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387302","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-10","<p>We do not hold information regarding power line failures to that level of disaggregation. Network Rail may have this information, and my Hon Friend may wish to contact them directly through Mark Carne, Chief Executive, Network Rail, 1 Eversholt Street, London, NW1 2DN.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","5341","2015-07-10T11:25:05.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387302/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387302/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-02","East Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many journeys have been affected by power line failures on the East Coast Main Line in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","5339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387303","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-07","<p>The Government remains committed to seeing an improvement in the provision of access services for video-on-demand (VoD) services. We have been monitoring progress of the provision of access services for VoD content since 2013 through engagement with the Authority for Television On Demand (ATVOD), platform operators and content providers. Government will use information from a variety of sources to develop a target that we would expect to see reached by mid-2016. That information includes the Action on Hearing Loss, Sense and RNIB paper (April 2015). If ATVOD's 2015 annual survey of VoD services indicates that significant progress has not been made then, as stated in the Connectivity, Content and Consumers Paper (July 2013), we will consider legislation in 2016.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-07T16:50:52.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387303/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387303/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-02","Video on Demand: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to the conclusions of his Department's report, Connectivity, Content and Consumers, published in July 2013, what progress has been made in establishing and enforcing targets on subtitled and audio-description TV services for on-demand content on the 80 per cent of on-demand providers in the UK who offer no subtitles at all.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","5522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387304","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-07-07","<p>The Government does not hold this type of information.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Royal Mail, as the designated Universal Service Provider for the United Kingdom, is required to provide the universal service to a specified standard and in accordance with quality targets agreed with and monitored by Ofcom, the independent regulator for postal services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The company publishes reports on its quality of service, which includes postcode areas, each quarter on its website.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-07-07T15:16:58.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387304/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387304/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-07-02","Postal Services: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what statistics he holds on (a) reliability of delivery and (b) success rate of Royal Mail post for (i) Cambridge and (ii) the UK.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","5498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387305","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-09","<p>Following discussions in November 2014, we are planning to deliver border security training to Tunisian Forces on the Libyan border later this year.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-07-09T15:09:54.06Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387305/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387305/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-02","Tunisia: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he has received a request from the Tunisian government for military training to improve border security between Tunisia and Libya.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","5343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387306","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-09","<p>Leisure aviation is an important part of the general aviation sector. In March 2015 the Coalition Government published a General Aviation Strategy which set out how the Government would work with this sector and this approach continues. Alongside this, the Government published economic research which estimated the sector, which includes tourism related activity such as leisure flying, gliding clubs and ballooning, is worth around £3 billion annually to the UK economy, and is responsible for around 38,000 jobs. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/general-aviation-strategy" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/general-aviation-strategy</a> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/general-aviation-economic-value" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/general-aviation-economic-value</a></p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-07-09T15:53:42.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387306/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387306/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-02","Tourism: Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made as to the effect of leisure aviation on the UK tourism sector; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","5436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387307","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-07-08","Since the 26 June terrorist attack in Sousse, The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) and The Secretary of State for the Home Department, my right hon. Friend the Member for Maidenhead (Mrs May) have spoken to their French counterparts and discussed areas in which we can work more closely together to support Tunisia. The Home Secretary and I also visited Tunisa with the French (and German) Interior Ministers on 29 June both to pay our respects to the victims of the Sousse attack and for discussions with the Tunisian Authorities.","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-07-08T13:01:34.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387307/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387307/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-07-02","Tunisia: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will hold discussions with his French counterpart on improving collaboration between the French and UK governments in providing governance and capability training for Tunisian national and regional government bodies.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","5352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387308","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-08","<p>DFID has not supported any inter-faith dialogue projects as such in Tunisia. However, under the joint FCO-DFID Arab Partnership Participation Fund (APPF), the UK funded the Centre for the Study of Islam and Democracy (CSID) in Tunisia to support the development of the constitution and the electoral process (£510,210 over the last two years). One component of this work involved promoting constructive dialogue between Islamists and Secularists.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-07-08T14:32:59.687Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387308/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387308/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-07-02","Tunisia: Community Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will work with the government of Tunisia to improve inter-faith dialogue.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","5344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387309","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>In the financial year 1 April 2014 to 31 March 2015, HM Passport Office generated an unplanned surplus of £59.075 million due to passport demand being significantly higher than forecast for the year. This figure is published in the Home Office’s Annual Report and Accounts 2014-15, and can be found at line G of the table on page 93 of the publication.</p><p>A copy of the Home Office’s Annual Report and Accounts 2014-15 is available in the Vote office of the House of Commons, and also on gov.uk website here: https://www.gov.uk/mwg internal/de5fs23hu73ds/progress?id=sBy1t6XS5Z1jNsMdhX20ktLGye4ndTbGKe5Pjr5O12o,&amp;dl</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-09T14:42:28.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387309/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387309/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","HM Passport Office: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what surplus was generated by HM Passport Agency between April 2014 and April 2015.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","5487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387310","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>To ensure the integrity and security of the UK border Her Majesty’s Government does not comment on port specific statistics.</p><p>At the regional juxtaposed ports in Northern France, around 40,000 attempts to cross the Channel illegally in 2014/15 have been prevented by Border Force and its contractors and the French authorities, compared to 18,000 in 2013/14.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-09T14:45:20.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387310/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387310/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Illegal Immigrants: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information she holds on how many illegal migrants have been located at Calais and Coquelles by (a) Border Force staff, (b) Eurotunnel and Eurostar staff, (c) ferry company staff and (d) the French authorities in each time period for which records are kept since January 2014.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","5259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387311","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>At the ports of Calais and Coquelles illegal migrants detected by Border Force are passed directly to the French police for removal from the UK control zones for processing by the French authorities.</p><p>To ensure the integrity and security of the UK border Her Majesty’s Government does not comment on port specific statistics.</p><p>At the regional juxtaposed ports in Northern France, around 40,000 attempts to cross the Channel illegally in 2014/15 have been prevented by Border Force and its contractors and the French authorities, compared to 18,000 in 2013/14.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-09T14:42:06.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387311/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387311/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Illegal Immigrants: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what records the Border Force keeps on illegal migrants prevented from entering the UK by UK authorities or companies at the Port of Calais and Coquelles.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","5260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387312","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>Records are not held centrally on the outcome of individual claims and data is not available in the format requested at (a), (b), and (i). In the financial year 2014-15, Her Majesty’s Passport Office (HM Passport Office) paid compensation totalling £250, 010.67.</p><p>HM Passport Office only normally offers compensation for financial loss as a result of delays in its guaranteed (Fast Track and Premium) services; or to reimburse any out of pocket expenses incurred by a customer as a direct consequence of an error or omission by a member of staff.</p><p>Full details on HMPO compensation can be found at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/compensation-and-complaints-handling</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-09T14:43:29.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387312/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387312/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many claims for compensation the Passport Office (a) approved and (b) rejected between April 2014 and April 2015; and how much compensation was (i) claimed and (ii) paid in relation to those claims in that period.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","5261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387313","Home Office","false","2015-07-13","<p>The total penalties paid and received by the Home Office under the Civil Penalty scheme for the Nord Pas de Calais region are £4.2 million in 2013/14 and £6.6 million in 2014/15. Border Force issued penalties for those attempting to enter the UK via the Pas de Calais region for each month since January 2014 as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td>Month</td><td>Number of Penalties Issued</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>January 2014</td><td>179</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>February 2014</td><td>157</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>March 2014</td><td>184</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>April 2014</td><td>221</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>May 2014</td><td>263</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>June 2014</td><td>282</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>July 2014</td><td>369</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>August 2014</td><td>335</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>September 2014</td><td>309</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>October 2014</td><td>333</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>November 2014</td><td>271</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>December 2014</td><td>254</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>January 2015</td><td>316</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>February 2015</td><td>186</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>March 2015</td><td>182</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>April 2015</td><td>198</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td>May 2015</td><td>268</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Two Codes of Practice govern what is expected of hauliers and drivers in preventing the carriage of clandestine entrants and the level of penalty that can be imposed in a given set of circumstances. If an effective system for preventing the carriage of clandestine entrants is in operation then no penalty would be imposed.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-07-13T11:46:39.75Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387313/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387313/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Illegal Immigrants: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many fines have been (a) imposed and (b) paid for the carrying of illegal migrants at ports of entry to the UK in the Pas de Calais region in each time period for which records are kept since January 2014.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","5262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387314","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-07-07","<p>As at December 2014, 253 outsourced staff, employed by contractors with the central Department to provide office and building services in the central Department and its agencies, were paid below the Living Wage.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Defra pays the living wage to all its permanent employees and I am working with my officials on plans to extend this to cover those staff who work for contractors.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-07-07T15:39:24.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387314/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387314/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-07-02","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to her Answer of 23 June 2015 to Question 3146, how many staff working at her Department for contractors do not earn the living wage; what services such staff deliver; and whether her Department plans to become an accredited living wage employer.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart McDonald","5521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387315","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-14","<p>An independent review of the sanctions regime for non-payment of the television licence has been led by David Perry QC on behalf of the Government. The Review has now concluded and the Report will be published in due course. In accordance with section 77(3) of the Deregulation Act 2015, I will lay a report setting out my response to the Review within 3 months of its completion.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-14T08:31:08.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387315/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387315/answer","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387315/answer/previousversion/13475","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-07-02","Television: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether he plans to remove criminal sanctions for non-payment of the television licence fee.","false","Biography information for Edward Argar","Charnwood","Edward Argar","5342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387316","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-07","<p /> <p>We are on track with our plans for the national roll out of Universal Credit to single claimants, couples and families. The Department is not setting targets for numbers in receipt of Universal Credit at various points in time. Final numbers will vary according to a number of factors such as economic circumstances over time and the behavioural change of claimants.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-07T15:26:33.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387316/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387316/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-02","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he now expects the number of claimants of universal credit to exceed (a) one per cent, (b) two per cent and (c) five per cent of all benefit claimants.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387317","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-07","<p /> <p> </p><p>The trial commenced on 20 April 2015 and therefore it is too early to make an assessment at this stage</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-07T15:27:34.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387317/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387317/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387317/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-02","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress has been made on the trials of support for in-work progression; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387318","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-07","<p /> <p>The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions made clear in his statement to the House on 1 July that Government is committed to eliminating child poverty, and improving children’s life chances. The Government’s new approach will focus on tackling the root causes of poverty, in particular worklessness and educational attainment.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will introduce legislation to give effect to this approach and to remove the existing measures and targets in the Child Poverty Act. Details of the legislation and the action the Government will take will be set out in due course.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-07T15:23:19.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387318/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387318/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387318/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-02","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will define new targets for child poverty.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387319","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-07","<p /> <p>This Government is committed to working to eliminate child poverty and improving life chances for children – now and in the future.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions announced on the 1<sup>st</sup> July that the Government will focus on tackling the root causes of child poverty.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will introduce legislation to give effect to this approach and to remove the existing measures and targets in the Child Poverty Act. Details of the legislation and the action the Government will take will be set out in due course.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-07T15:25:21.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387319/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387319/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387319/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-07-02","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what requirements will be placed on Government agencies in the legislation which is proposed to replace the Child Poverty Act 2010.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387320","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-10","<p>We are aware that the custom and practice for some 4 axle rigid volumetric concrete mixers in recent years has been to operate in excess of the 32 tonne weight limit specified in regulations. A consultation earlier this year about the scope of exemptions from annual roadworthiness testing for some types of Heavy Goods Vehicles sought views about whether a higher weight limit could be set for such vehicles to avoid dislocation in the market. We have the responses to the consultation now and are considering this issue.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-10T10:22:30.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387320/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387320/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387320/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-02","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy is on applying a 32 tonne weight limit to volumetric vehicles.","false","Biography information for Simon Hoare","North Dorset","Simon Hoare","5410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387321","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-10","<p>Both the consultations took place between 11<sup>th</sup> December 2014 and 5<sup>th</sup> March 2015. I hope to publish the responses received to the consultations soon. The consultations were published by the last Government and we will need to consider the way forward before a full Departmental response can be published.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-10T10:26:10.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387321/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387321/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-07-02","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects to publish his Department's response to its consultations on the (a) review of HGV periodic testing and inspection exemptions and (b) goods vehicle operating licensing exemptions.","false","Biography information for Simon Hoare","North Dorset","Simon Hoare","5440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387322","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice (Table 10 of annual reports). They are available here <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>. These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used by each government department. Both sections 38(1)(a) and 38(1)(b) were used by DFID in all such cases.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-07-09T11:39:27.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387322/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387322/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-07-02","Department for International Development: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, on how many occasions her Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387323","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice (Table 10 of annual reports). They are available here <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>. These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used by each government department. Both sections 38(1)(a) and 38(1)(b) were used by DFID in all such cases.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-07-09T11:40:14.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387323/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387323/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387323/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-07-02","Department for International Development: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, on how many occasions her Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387324","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-10","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice on a quarterly and annual basis. They are available via the following link and include up to the first quarter of 2015:</p><p> </p><p><a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used across all monitored bodies. The table below outlines the number of times s.38 has been used broken down by subsection. Figures for 2010 show only the total number of times s.38 has been used as the records themselves have been destroyed in line with the Department’s record retention policy:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>s.38 (1) (a)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>s.38 (1) (b)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>s.38 (1) (a) &amp; (b)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>* records are no longer held for 2010.</em></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","5290","2015-07-10T09:53:58.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387324/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387324/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-02","Ministry of Justice: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387325","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-10","<p /> <p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice on a quarterly and annual basis. They are available via the following link and include up to the first quarter of 2015:</p><p> </p><p><a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used across all monitored bodies. The table below outlines the number of times s.38 has been used broken down by subsection. Figures for 2010 show only the total number of times s.38 has been used as the records themselves have been destroyed in line with the Department’s record retention policy:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>s.38 (1) (a)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>s.38 (1) (b)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>s.38 (1) (a) &amp; (b)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>* records are no longer held for 2010.</em></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","5311","2015-07-10T09:53:58.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387325/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387325/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-02","Ministry of Justice: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387326","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-07-09","<p>The Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <a href="http://www.justuce.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justuce.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-07-09T15:38:18.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387326/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387326/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-07-02","Ministry of Justice: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what instructions have been given to staff in his Department dealing with freedom of information requests on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No. 19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, in considering whether to apply the exemptions in section 38 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387327","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>No Northern Ireland Office (NIO) specific guidance has been issued to staff on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19, issued by the Information Commissioner’s Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, NIO staff responsible for preparing FOI responses regularly refer to ICO and MOJ Guidance on the application of exemptions.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-07-09T11:44:09.17Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387327/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387327/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-02","Northern Ireland Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what instructions have been given to staff in her Department dealing with freedom of information requests on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No. 19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, in considering whether to apply the exemptions in section 38 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387328","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>The Department does not separately record use of exemptions under section 38(a) and 38(b), but does record use of section 38 as a whole. During the past 5 years this exemption was used three times in 2010, three times in 2013 and not used in 2011, 2012 and 2014.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice (Table 10 of annual reports). They are available here:</p><p><a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</strong></a><em>. </em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","5312","2015-07-09T11:48:40.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387328/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387328/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-02","Northern Ireland Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, on how many occasions her Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387329","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>No such instructions have been issued. Officials handling freedom of information requests are advised to consult the guidance issued by the Information Commissioner’s Office whenever the use of an application is being considered.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice publishes annual statistical reports on the handling of requests for information under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 for central government. These reports include statistics on the number of times each exemption was used by each government department to withhold information. These reports can be accessed on the following webpage: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","5288 ; 5309","2015-07-09T13:51:43.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387329/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387329/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Home Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what instructions have been given to staff in her Department dealing with freedom of information requests on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No. 19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, in considering whether to apply the exemptions in section 38 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387330","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-09","<p>No guidance has been issued to staff on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-07-09T11:40:57.633Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387330/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387330/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-07-02","Department for International Development: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what instructions have been given to staff in her Department dealing with freedom of information requests on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No. 19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, in considering whether to apply the exemptions in section 38 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387331","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>No such instructions have been issued. Officials handling freedom of information requests are advised to consult the guidance issued by the Information Commissioner’s Office whenever the use of an application is being considered.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice publishes annual statistical reports on the handling of requests for information under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 for central government. These reports include statistics on the number of times each exemption was used by each government department to withhold information. These reports can be accessed on the following webpage: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","5288 ; 5330","2015-07-09T13:51:43.853Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387331/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387331/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Home Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, on how many occasions her Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387332","Home Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>No such instructions have been issued. Officials handling freedom of information requests are advised to consult the guidance issued by the Information Commissioner’s Office whenever the use of an application is being considered.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice publishes annual statistical reports on the handling of requests for information under the Freedom of Information Act 2000 for central government. These reports include statistics on the number of times each exemption was used by each government department to withhold information. These reports can be accessed on the following webpage: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","5309 ; 5330","2015-07-09T13:51:43.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387332/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387332/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-07-02","Home Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, on how many occasions her Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387333","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice in their annual reports on FOI Statistics (Table 10). The annual reports are available here</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used by each Government Department, including the Ministry of Defence. More detailed figures for the constituent parts of section 38 are not readily available because our systems are not designed to provide a more detailed breakdown than is required for the published statistics.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","5302","2015-07-09T15:06:52.397Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387333/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387333/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-02","Ministry of Defence: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387334","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-09","<p>The Ministry of Defence issues guidance to Freedom of Information practitioners on the use of section 38, along with other exemptions. This guidance is attached.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-07-09T15:12:43.48Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387334/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387334/answer","20120925-CN34-Section38-HealthandSafety.pdf","20120925-CN34-Section38-HealthandSafety.pdf","5323 - Section 38 of the FOI Act - Health & Safety","5323 - Section 38 of the FOI Act - Health & Safety","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387334/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-07-02","Ministry of Defence: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what instructions have been given to staff in his Department dealing with freedom of information requests on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No. 19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, in considering whether to apply the exemptions in section 38 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5323"
