ent/collections/government-foi-statistics</a><em>. </em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used by each government department.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>No guidance has been issued to staff on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a>.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland","5277 ; 5319","2015-07-08T10:10:08.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387362/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387362/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387362/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-07-02","Attorney General: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, on how many occasions the Law Officers' Departments applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387363","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions (including the use of Section 38) are published by the Ministry of Justice. They are available here <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a></p><p>More detailed figures for the constituent parts of section 38 could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The Cabinet Office has not issued guidance to staff on the application of “Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19”, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <em><a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a></em></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","5278 ; 5299","2015-07-09T14:59:43.353Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387363/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387363/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-02","Cabinet Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what instructions have been given to staff in his Department dealing with freedom of information requests on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No. 19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, in considering whether to apply the exemptions in section 38 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387364","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions (including the use of Section 38) are published by the Ministry of Justice. They are available here <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a></p><p>More detailed figures for the constituent parts of section 38 could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The Cabinet Office has not issued guidance to staff on the application of “Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19”, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <em><a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a></em></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","5299 ; 5320","2015-07-09T14:59:43.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387364/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387364/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-02","Cabinet Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387365","Cabinet Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions (including the use of Section 38) are published by the Ministry of Justice. They are available here <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</a></p><p>More detailed figures for the constituent parts of section 38 could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The Cabinet Office has not issued guidance to staff on the application of “Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19”, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <em><a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a></em></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","5278 ; 5320","2015-07-09T14:59:43.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387365/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387365/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-07-02","Cabinet Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387366","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-10","<p>Section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 was used by HM Treasury on the following number of occasions in the last 5 years: 2011: 1.</p><p> </p><p>- Section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 was used by HM Treasury on the following numbers of occasions in each of the last 5 years: 2010: 2; 2011: 3; 2012: 1; 2013: 0; 2014: 1.</p><p> </p><p>- Sections 38(1)(a) and (b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 were used together on the following numbers of occasions in each of the last 5 years: 2013: 2.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>No guidance has been issued to staff on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a>.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","5315 ; 5336","2015-07-10T12:47:10.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387366/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387366/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-02","Treasury: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387367","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-10","<p>Section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 was used by HM Treasury on the following number of occasions in the last 5 years: 2011: 1.</p><p> </p><p>- Section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 was used by HM Treasury on the following numbers of occasions in each of the last 5 years: 2010: 2; 2011: 3; 2012: 1; 2013: 0; 2014: 1.</p><p> </p><p>- Sections 38(1)(a) and (b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 were used together on the following numbers of occasions in each of the last 5 years: 2013: 2.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>No guidance has been issued to staff on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a>.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","5294 ; 5336","2015-07-10T12:47:10.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387367/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387367/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-02","Treasury: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387368","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-10","<p>Section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 was used by HM Treasury on the following number of occasions in the last 5 years: 2011: 1.</p><p> </p><p>- Section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 was used by HM Treasury on the following numbers of occasions in each of the last 5 years: 2010: 2; 2011: 3; 2012: 1; 2013: 0; 2014: 1.</p><p> </p><p>- Sections 38(1)(a) and (b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 were used together on the following numbers of occasions in each of the last 5 years: 2013: 2.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>No guidance has been issued to staff on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No.19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, about the application of section 38 of the Act. However, the Ministry of Justice has published its own guidance on the use of this exemption. This is available here: <a title="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/information-access-rights/foi-guidance-for-practitioners/exemptions-guidance</a>.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","5294 ; 5315","2015-07-10T12:47:10.43Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387368/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387368/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-07-02","Treasury: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what instructions have been given to staff in his Department dealing with freedom of information requests on the application of Freedom of Information Act Awareness Guidance No. 19, issued by the Information Commissioner's Office, in considering whether to apply the exemptions in section 38 of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387369","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>The Department does not separately record use of exemptions under section 38(a) and 38(b), but does record use of section 38 as a whole. During the past 5 years this exemption was used three times in 2010, three times in 2013 and not used in 2011, 2012 and 2014.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice (Table 10 of annual reports). They are available here:</p><p><a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</strong></a><em>. </em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","5291","2015-07-09T11:48:40.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387369/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387369/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-07-02","Northern Ireland Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, on how many occasions her Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387370","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice (Table 10 of annual reports). They are available here:</p><p><a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</strong></a><em>. </em></p><p>These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used by each government department. More detailed figures for the constituent parts of section 38 are not readily available because our systems are not designed to provide a more detailed breakdown than is required for the published statistics.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-09T11:32:18.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387370/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387370/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-02","Scotland Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(b) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the safety of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387371","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-09","<p>Statistics on the use of Freedom of Information exemptions are published by the Ministry of Justice (Table 10 of annual reports), and are available here:</p><p><a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</strong></a><em>. </em></p><p>These statistics provide the number of times section 38 as a whole has been used by each government department. More detailed figures for the constituent parts of section 38 are not readily available because our systems are not designed to provide a more detailed breakdown than is required for the published statistics.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-09T11:34:13.04Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387371/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/387371/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-07-02","Scotland Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, on how many occasions his Department applied the exemption in section 38(1)(a) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000 (disclosure likely to endanger the physical or mental health of any individual) in wholly or partly refusing a freedom of information request in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","5292"
